\n< Okar >This is the job description.
\n< Okar >The buyer for a certain item will be coming soon.

\n< Okar >We are tense... or rather, I should say we are in
a hostile relationship.

\n< Okar >However, precisely because of our relationship,
the profits from this business are huge.

\n< Okar >Taboos can be profitable. However, we must never
let our guard down.

\n< Okar >We are both calculating the timing to cut each
other. Or rather, waiting for the timing when the
other person will make a move.

\n< Okar >Before being betrayed, I have to betray. But the
deal is sweet. I want to continue. Until the very
last moment.

\n< Okar >Here, a delicate balance is born. A precarious
equilibrium. Do you understand?
\n< Serena >What should I do?

\n< Okar >I want you to mediate the deal. No, I'm not asking
you to talk.

\n< Okar >Rather, stay silent. Don't speak. Don't do
anything unnecessary.

\n< Okar >During the transaction, we and they will face each
other in confrontation. You will step forward from
our ranks, hand over the goods to them, receive
the money, and come back. It's simple, right?

\n< Serena >In the event that something happens, it means I
will be the first one to die.

\n< Okar >Hehehe... Well, don't take it so badly. If it's
your prideful armor, you should be able to handle
it somehow, right?
\n< Serena >Maybe.
\n< Okar >Hmph, you're not cute at all, kid.
\n< Okar >Oh, you've come. Do well, okay?

\n< Serena >....

\n< Serena >(...Who are these people... Foreigners,
infidels...?)
\n< Serena >(Is the guild doing business with infidels?)

\n< Serena >(Idiots... This goes against both the country's
law and the church's law. This is a major crime.)
\n< Okar >...Hey, hey.

\n< Okar >Don't just stand there. Deliver the goods. We're
going to pull the carriage all the way to their
place.
\n< Serena >...I understand.
\n< Male Infidel >＃＃＃＃.＃＃？＃＃＃＃.
\n< Serena >What? What are you saying?
\n< Serena >Are you laughing?

\n< Serena >A unique body odor... It's a rough, medicinal
smell.
\n< Serena >The scent of infidels... Unpleasant...
\n< Male Infidel >＃＃＃.＃＃.＃＃＃＃.
\n< Serena >It's the payment. Hand it over.
\n< Serena >Ugh!? It's heavy...! Is this... a gold bar!?

\n< Serena >How much value does this amount represent... What
kind of product can be exchanged for this gold
bar...?

\n< Serena >So they were selling people, women, and children
to foreign countries.
\n< Serena >Hehehe. I see.

\n< Serena >...I had a slight uneasiness. Confusion. It would
have been deliberately failing the request.

\n< Serena >Is it okay for me to inconvenience the guild for
my own convenience? Is it okay for me to disregard
someone's wish?

\n< Serena >But if it's this kind of request! If it's this
kind of job!
\n< Serena >I will gladly fail! I will ruin everything!!
\n< Serena >Not a single finger shall touch this carriage!!

\n< Okar >Uooo?! What is it?! What is it?!

\n< Serena >...Defeat the infidels, free the girls, and let
myself be captured.
\n< Serena >Well, I must show them that I can do it well...!

\n< Okar >Shit! Shit! Stupid brats!! Why the hell...!
Dammit! Everyone, draw your weapons! It's war! We
have no choice but to fight!

\n< Okar >Dammit!!!
ストーリー　物資護衛依頼 勝利

\n< Serena >...So you left. You even conveniently took the
gold bars with you.
\n< Okar >Hey, you brat...
\n< Serena >Ah, Lord Okar. You're alive. This is unexpected.
\n< Okar >What the...!?

\n< Okar >I'll ruin this deal! The gold will be lost! The
women have escaped!

\n< Okar >Do you understand? This is a huge loss... I'll be
erased from the guild... No, something even worse
will happen.

\n< Serena >I apologize. I let my emotions get the best of me.
I will report this to the guild as my
responsibility.
\n< Okar >Of course! You guys, catch this brat!

\n< Okar >Shit... This huge failure... Even if I blame it on
the kid, will the guild let me off the hook...?
Shit, damn it...!
\n< Okar >At least, I'll make this kid mine...

\n< Serena >It's in your best interest to come quietly. Don't
do anything unnecessary.

\n< Serena >You must have witnessed the battle earlier. I
still have plenty of energy left.
\n< Okar >...Shit! The guild! We're taking you with us!

\n< Okar >Ahh! Shut up! Is that all you've got!? Is that
all, huh!?

\n< Serena >...Well then. We can say that the first phase was
a success for now.

\n< Serena >Let's pray that Cecilia can guide us well from
here on.
